symc.name: ICU_BROWSER_MODE
symc.desc: Does not encode or decode characters after "#" or "?", and does not remove trailing white space after "?". If this value is not specified, the entire URL is encoded and trailing white space is removed.

symc.name: ICU_DECODE
symc.desc: Converts all %XX sequences to characters, including escape sequences, before the URL is parsed.

symc.name: ICU_ENCODE_PERCENT
symc.desc: Encodes any percent signs encountered. By default, percent signs are not encoded. This value is available in Microsoft Internet Explorer 5 and later.

symc.name: ICU_NO_ENCODE
symc.desc: Does not convert unsafe characters to escape sequences.

symc.name: ICU_NO_META
symc.desc: Does not remove meta sequences (such as "." and "..") from the URL.
